NAME
       dmesg - print or control the kernel ring buffer

SYNOPSIS
       dmesg [options]

DESCRIPTION
       dmesg is used to examine or control the kernel ring buffer.

OPTIONS
       -C, --clear
              clear the kernel ring buffer

       -c, --read-clear
              read and clear all messages

       -d, --show-delta
              show time delta between printed messages

       -e, --reltime
              show local time and time delta in readable format

       -F, --file=FILE
              use FILE instead of the kernel log buffer

       -f, --facility=LIST
              restrict output to defined facilities (comma-separated):
              kern, mail, daemon, auth, syslog, lpr, news, uucp, cron,
              authpriv, ftp, local0-local7

       -H, --human
              human-readable output (enables reltime format)

       -h, --help
              display this help and exit

       -k, --kernel
              display kernel messages

       -l, --level=LIST
              restrict output to defined levels (comma-separated):
              emerg, alert, crit, err, warn, notice, info, debug

       -n, --console-level=LEVEL
              set level of messages printed to console (not supported)

       --noescape
              don't escape unprintable characters

       -P, --nopager
              do not pipe output into a pager

       -r, --raw
              print the raw message buffer

       -s, --buffer-size=SIZE
              buffer size to query the kernel ring buffer (default 256K)

       -T, --ctime
              show human-readable timestamp

       -t, --notime
              don't show any timestamp with messages

       --time-format=FORMAT
              show timestamp using FORMAT: delta, reltime, ctime, notime,
              iso

       -u, --userspace
              display userspace messages

       -V, --version
              output version information and exit

       -w, --follow
              wait for new messages (poll every 1 second)

       -x, --decode
              decode facility and level to readable strings

NOTES
       Default behavior shows kernel-only messages.  The default buffer
       size is 256KB.  -H implies reltime display.

AUTHORS
       LikeOS-64 project.

SEE ALSO
       ps(1), free(1), uptime(1)

